cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG 

The paper deals with the problem of cross-media retrieval, which is a topic that falls under multiple sub-categories of computer science. The use of neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests that the paper could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia), while the focus on information retrieval and similarity search suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of visual and textual modalities and the emphasis on image and text processing suggest cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the use of constraints and optimization techniques suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category.
